The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for skin lesion segmentation, which falls under the scope of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of GrabCut algorithm and evaluation of performance metrics also suggest the relevance of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of color space for segmentation indicates the relevance of multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
